  "title": "Crawler Crane Operator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Why join us</strong></p><ul><li>5.5 work day</li><li>Sign on incentive up to 1.5k! (depending on years of experience)</li><li>Supportive work environment where safety and teamwork is key</li><li>Familiarization training will be provided</li></ul><p>JOB DESCRIPTION:</p><ul><li>Safely operate the assigned crane, maintaining a high level of awareness and attention to detail at all times.</li><li>Perform routine maintenance tasks such as lubrication, greasing, and cleaning to ensure the crane is in top working condition.</li><li>Conduct daily checks to confirm the crane is safe to operate, ensuring any malfunctions, wear, or damage are promptly reported.</li><li>Follow all in-house site regulations and report any unsafe job requests to the site in charge.</li><li>Collaborate with the team and supervisors to maintain a safe and efficient work environment.</li><li>Perform additional duties as assigned to support the team and site operations</li></ul><p>JOB REQUIREMENTS:</p><ul><li>Minimum of 5 years working experience as crane operator</li><li>Valid crane operator certification (MOM registered, BCA approved)</li><li>Strong commitment to safety</li><li>Willing to work on weekends and Public Holidays, when required, with overtime.</li><li>Valid Safety orientation course certificate</li></ul><p>Interested candidates, please call 6560 7788 for interview arrangements.</p>",
